# Publishing Sonar Mag articles

Content is **Supabase rows only** — insert/update `articles` and the live Astro site picks it up (short CDN cache). No redeploy for copy.

## Required read

Before writing prose, open and follow [docs/anti-slop-manifesto.md](docs/anti-slop-manifesto.md).

## Homepage (automatic)

| Field | Effect |
| --- | --- |
| `status = 'published'` | Eligible for the board |
| `is_highlighted = true` | Eligible for the **large splash hero** (newest highlighted wins) |
| everything else | Fills secondary → opinion → dark card → Latest by `published_at` |
| `popular_rank` | Optional Popular rail (1 = top) |

You do **not** set `featured_slot` for splash layout anymore.

## Row fields to set

- `slug` (unique), `title`, `excerpt`, `ticker`
  - Splash/opinion cards show the first two body paragraphs in two columns (line-clamped). Write those openings for the card.
  - Titles must pass the manifesto clarity test: clever tone without a clear case still fails.
- `author_id`, `category_id`
- `hero_image`, `hero_alt`, `thumb_image`
- `read_minutes`, `listen_minutes`, `published_at`, `published_label`
- `paragraphs` jsonb blocks (strings and optional `{ type: "tweet", ... }`)
- `is_highlighted` boolean
- optional: `highlight_word` + `highlight_tone` (`red` \| `tan`) for title mark

## Tweet embeds

```json
{
  "type": "tweet",
  "url": "https://x.com/Handle/status/123",
  "authorName": "Display Name",
  "authorHandle": "Handle",
  "text": "Full tweet text…",
  "postedAt": "2026-07-20T10:56:59.000Z"
}
```

Fetch via syndication/fxtwitter when X HTML 403s. Never load Twitter widgets.js.

## Skill

For a two-article batch (one highlighted), use the project skill `write-sonar-articles`.
